examples.korean: As scarce as truth is, the supply has always been in excess of the demand. (Josh Billings) 발음듣기 진실이 비록 흔치 않으나, 공급이 언제나 수요를 초과해 왔다. (조쉬 빌링스, 지혜명언) 명언/속담

examples.korean: But while many singles say they don't mind keeping a backup, hardly anyone likes to be treated like one. 발음듣기 그러나 다수의 독신들은 백업을 두는 것에 대해 별 신경이 쓰이지 않으나 백업으로 취급 받는 것은 싫다고 말했다. Neungyule

examples.korean: She says she does not regret her past, but it was very hard to be away from her daughter while she was in prison. 발음듣기 그녀는 과거를 후회하지는 않으나 수감 기간 동안 딸과 떨어져 있는 게 매우 힘들었다고 말한다. Neungyule
examples.english: She says she does not regret her past, but it was very hard to be away from her daughter while she was in prison. 발음

examples.korean: Although they are not included on the list of the IWC moratorium, South Korea has banned the killing of whales and dolphins. 발음듣기 한국은 IWC의 포경금지 대상에 포함되지는 않으나 고래와 돌고래잡이를 금지해왔다. Neungyule
examples.english: Although they are not included on the list of the IWC moratorium, South Korea has banned the killing of whales and dolphins. 발음

examples.korean: Seoul citizens are unhappy about the situation, but the city government says that the fare hike is inevitable. 발음듣기 서울 시민들은 이를 달갑게 여기지 않으나 서울시 측은 요금 인상은 불가피하다는 입장이다. Neungyule
